To update the NUI score when an event is triggered in Lua, you can follow these steps:

1. First, create an event in your server-side Lua script. In this example, let's call the event "updateScore":

```lua
 RegisterNetEvent('updateScore')
 AddEventHandler('updateScore', function(newScore)
     -- Code to update the NUI will be added here
 end)
```

2. Create a function in your client-side JavaScript (main.js) to update the score:

```javascript
function updateScore(newScore) {
    document.getElementById('score').innerText = newScore;
}
```

3. Add a function in your client-side JavaScript to listen for the "updateScore" event and call the `updateScore()` function:

```javascript
window.addEventListener('message', (event) => {
    if (event.data.type === 'updateScore') {
        updateScore(event.data.newScore);
    }
});
```

4. Now, from your server-side Lua script, you can trigger the "updateScore" event to update the NUI score:

```lua
-- Send the event to the client-side script, passing the new score value
-- Replace "newScoreValue" with the actual score you want to display
TriggerClientEvent('updateScore', source, newScoreValue)
```

When the "updateScore" event is triggered on the server-side, it will pass the new score value to the client-side script, which will then update the NUI score with the given value.

